dl.instructions.1: This tool downloads, from the loaded layers, the visible elements on the map. Does not download the entire layer. To download the entire layer, press the information button [i] attached to each layer or group of layers in the panel of loaded layers. Also, does not download the items created with the drawing tool. These can be downloaded using the [arrow down] button of the same drawing tool.
dl.instructions.1.1: To download the visible elements, place the map in the desired area, load the layers of interest, select the desired output format and click Download.
dl.instructions.2: It is only possible to download data from layers that are loaded, visible on the map and that are owned by the Insular Council or the City Councils. Elements of layers from other IDE nodes will not be downloaded (IDEIB, Catastre, Costs ...).
dl.instructions.3: Each download may include data from several layers, which will be included in a compressed zip or kmz extension file for service
dl.instructions.4: There is a limitation on the number of items to download. When this limit is exceeded, a message will indicate to the user that he needs to reduce the number of items to download. This can be done in two ways:
dl.instructions.5: Increasing the zoom to define a smaller area.
dl.instructions.6: Reducing the number of layers loaded.
